Choking isn't specific to football or any one sport.  It means not being able to play at your highest level when it matters the most, such as in a championship game.

Some top stars are nevertheless prone to choking; others are not.  That may explain various sports dynasties.  Some teams perennially get into the playoffs; others perennially are the last team standing.  Often it's because their key players don't choke.

